    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.37a.37"/>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        505 <hi rend="caps">N.</hi> Brown
                        Minden, Nebr.
                        May 24, 1973
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Stan has perhaps already told you that one of our Minden sopho-mores took a number of pictures the afternoon we spent in your home two weeks ago. He will send one or two of them to you within the next week or so, as a little remembrance of what for us was a most rewarding experience.</p>
                
                <p>All of us here in Minden do really appreciate your kindness, and that of Mr. and Mrs. Young, in making us so welcome in your home.</p>
                
                <p>We would be happy to have Stan on our teaching staff, even if he had never met you. I must admit, however, that the role he has played as a link between us and you is one more big plus in his favor.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Marian L. Sinnis</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">27</fw>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
